00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:17,375
to Headquarters from area 17.

195
00:18:17,458 --> 00:18:19,416
We have located an API1.

196
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:23,416
Repeat, Young Star
2 has located an API1.

197
00:18:26,416 --> 00:18:28,541
Do you think we'll
be able to land?

198
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,083
We landed.

199
00:18:51,458 --> 00:18:53,333
Seems to me that we fell.

200
00:19:01,666 --> 00:19:02,958
Why did you
ignore the order and

201
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:05,333
rescue the Neo U.N. recon plane?

202
00:19:05,416 --> 00:19:06,750
I apologize.

203
00:19:07,666 --> 00:19:09,750
It was all my fault.

204
00:19:11,375 --> 00:19:12,541
Is it really such a bad thing to

205
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:14,833
rescue someone
when they're in need?

206
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:20,291
Well that all depends
on the situation.

207
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:35,625
So what do you think?

208
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:38,458
Was I too lenient with them?

209
00:19:39,208 --> 00:19:41,625
Well, you are the commander.

210
00:19:50,666 --> 00:19:52,000
Soshi!

211
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:11,291
Good work guys!

212
00:20:12,458 --> 00:20:14,458
The two of you
were simply amazing!

213
00:20:14,541 --> 00:20:15,666
You really did it.

214
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:17,083
You guys saved us.

215
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:18,583
Anyway, I'm glad
that the both of you

216
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:20,625
made it back here
safe and sound.

217
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:21,666
That's right.

218
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:22,833
I think it's great...

219
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:25,916
Don't mind me,
I'm just happy that's all.

220
00:20:27,208 --> 00:20:28,875
All right then guys,
I better take off.

221
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:30,541
I still have my training to do.

222
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:32,958
I gotta learn how to become
as useful as you two.

223
00:20:33,041 --> 00:20:36,125
Otherwise I might just
get kicked off the island.

224
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:44,000
He said we saved all of them.

225
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:47,166
But the truth is
we were rescued,

226
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:50,000
by those small flying machines.

227
00:20:56,791 --> 00:20:58,250
Koyo!

228
00:20:58,333 --> 00:21:00,083
And where have
you been all this time?

229
00:21:00,166 --> 00:21:01,125
Mamoru.

230
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:02,666
Kazuki and Soshi
fought this battle.

231
00:21:02,750 --> 00:21:03,666
You should've seen it.

232
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:04,875
It was awesome!

233
00:21:04,958 --> 00:21:06,375
Is that so?

234
00:21:07,083 --> 00:21:08,583
I expected that.

235
00:21:08,666 --> 00:21:10,208
This awesome thing
came out at the end

236
00:21:10,291 --> 00:21:11,958
and did this incredibly
awesome stuff.

237
00:21:12,041 --> 00:21:13,791
The whole thing
was just so awesome!

238
00:21:13,875 --> 00:21:15,166
You know what?

239
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:16,583
I'm sure that they have
some awesome footage of it.

240
00:21:16,666 --> 00:21:19,208
You should go and ask
Miss Kariya to show it to you.

241
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:21,000
I think I'd better not.

242
00:21:21,083 --> 00:21:23,708
I might get nervous and
lose confidence.

243
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:31,541
These are the coordinates that
were reported by Young Star 2.

244
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:36,583
So we finally found it.

245
00:21:36,666 --> 00:21:38,916
The island of Giants.

246
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:57,541
When I started this
day I never expected

247
00:21:57,625 --> 00:21:59,666
that it would end up like this.

248
00:22:05,208 --> 00:22:08,166
It takes a mature sailor
to move an old ship,

249
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:10,041
not a young sailor.

250
00:22:10,958 --> 00:22:15,583
But, the one to find a new
route is always a young sailor.

251
00:22:16,083 --> 00:22:18,708
However, the sailing map we

252
00:22:18,791 --> 00:22:23,583
found was a journey
filled with hardships...

253
00:22:24,916 --> 00:22:27,708
...which fell from the sky.

254
00:22:32,375 --> 00:22:37,333
♪ closing song ♪

255
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:38,166
Tatsumiya Island set sail.

256
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:40,250
We don't know where we're going.

257
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:42,500
We can't see what's ahead of us.

258
00:23:42,583 --> 00:23:45,583
And yet we're forced
to take a new step.

259
00:23:46,708 --> 00:23:51,791
And at that time,
two people exchange words.

260
00:23:51,875 --> 00:23:56,500
Next on "Fafner"
episode number five...

261
00:23:56,583 --> 00:23:58,375
Pledge.

262
00:23:59,625 --> 00:24:01,375
Are you there?

